cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with the task of temporal action localization in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture that involves multi-dilation temporal convolution blocks, which suggests that it could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) as well. The use of sub-networks with different dilation parameters and the formulation of boundary point detection indicate that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on two video benchmarks, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
